verbose_text: In the 2050-climate, averaged air temperature and global radiation increased compared to the baseline-climate by 2.1 degreesC and 6.7% respectively in the UK, and 1.9 degreesC and 1.1% respectively in NZ, whereas the decrease in annual precipitation was small (< 2%) in both the UK and NZ (XREF_FIG).
evidence: air temperature and global radiation increased compared to the baseline-climate by 2.1 degreesC and 6.7% respectively in the UK
